        "patch":  "@@ -0,0 +1,140 @@\n+# Correction Packet\n+\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-132\n+AUTHOR: Planner / OpenAI Codex\n+TIMESTAMP: 2026-05-23_22-55-20+0300\n+RELATED_FILES:\n+- ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md\n+- ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_*.md\n+- crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs\n+- crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs\n+STATUS: CORRECTION_OPEN\n+\n+## References\n+\n+- Task Packet: `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_TASK_2026-05-23_22-32-44+0300.md`\n+- Latest Execution Report: `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md`\n+- Latest Codex Control Review: `.ai/dispatch-ISSUE-132/codex.control.round0.json`\n+- Prior Correction Packets: none\n+\n+## Approved Corrections (Planner Sign-Off)\n+\n+The Executor MUST act on exactly these corrections - nothing more, nothing\n+less. Each correction references the specific Codex control review finding it\n+addresses.\n+\n+1. **Replace the invalid `Ctrl+0` reset premise** - Codex control finding:\n+   Q2/Q5 select `Ctrl+0` reset-to-default as the smallest user-visible\n+   `CommandBus::submit` action, but the report\u0027s own evidence shows no\n+   production caller can make `TimeScale` non-default today. From a normal\n+   fresh editor, resetting to `TimeScale::DEFAULT` would hit the existing\n+   `EditorShell::set_time_scale` no-op short-circuit and would not submit an\n+   action. Required change: revise Q2, Q3, and Q5 so the selected follow-up is\n+   a genuinely user-visible World-only `CommandBus::submit` action that\n+   submits from normal production state, or provide concrete code evidence\n+   that an existing production path can make the proposed `Ctrl+0` reset\n+   non-noop before the user invokes it. If no eligible candidate can be proven,\n+   the corrected EXEC report must follow the TASK packet\u0027s `NEEDS_HUMAN`\n+   route. Acceptance: Q2 no longer claims a fresh-editor `Ctrl+0` reset is a\n+   valid submitting action unless the report cites a production non-defaulting\n+   path; Q3 describes only the corrected Approach A implementation shape; Q5\n+   names one bounded follow-up task only if the non-noop, user-visible,\n+   World-only submit path is evidenced, otherwise Q5 says `NEEDS_HUMAN` and\n+   names the smallest human decision needed.\n+2. **Correct the production `Action` inventory** - Codex control finding: the\n+   EXEC report states `SetTimeScale` is the only production `Action` impl, but\n+   `crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs` contains production\n+   `CompoundAction` and `impl Action for CompoundAction`. Required change:\n+   update the Q1/source inventory and any command-log conclusions so they do\n+   not claim `SetTimeScale` is the only production `Action` implementation.\n+   Classify `CompoundAction` accurately as infrastructure/non-candidate if it\n+   has no direct user-visible production trigger in the audited roots.\n+   Acceptance: the corrected EXEC report explicitly names `CompoundAction`,\n+   cites `crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs`, and distinguishes production\n+   infrastructure actions from eligible user-visible candidates.\n+3. **Fix the search/tooling log claim** - Codex control finding: the EXEC\n+   report claims shell `rg` availability and `rg --files` usage, while the\n+   review environment reports `rg` unavailable and the report appears to have\n+   used Claude Grep/Glob tooling for several searches. Required change: make\n+   the command log/tooling section accurate. Do not claim `command -v rg`,\n+   shell `rg`, or `rg --files` ran unless they actually ran in the Executor\u0027s\n+   shell. If Claude Grep/Glob tooling was used, label it as tool-level search,\n+   not shell `rg`. If additional read-only searches are needed for the\n+   corrected report, use PowerShell fallbacks such as `Get-ChildItem` and\n+   `Select-String` when `rg` is unavailable. Acceptance: the corrected command\n+   log clearly separates shell commands from agent search tools, records any\n+   fallback used, and contains no unsupported claim that `rg` was available.\n+\n+## Deferred Findings (NOT Approved for This Round)\n+\n+None.\n+\n+## Updated Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+- The dispatch remains audit-only. No source, tests, docs, schemas, scripts,\n+  manifests, lockfiles, workflows, doctrine files, status files, GitHub state,\n+  or prior packets are authorized for editing by this correction.\n+- The correction round must produce a corrected EXEC report only, following the\n+  orchestrator\u0027s normal EXEC-packet behavior. The prior TASK, prior EXEC, and\n+  this CORRECT packet must not be rewritten.\n+- The corrected EXEC report must still contain the exact five-question answer\n+  block required by the TASK packet.\n+- The corrected Q1 inventory must include `CompoundAction` as a production\n+  `Action` implementation and classify it accurately.\n+- The corrected Q2/Q3/Q5 answer must not pick a default-reset action that is a\n+  no-op from normal fresh editor state unless the report cites production code\n+  that first makes the resource non-default.\n+- If no genuinely user-visible, World-only, non-noop `CommandBus::submit`\n+  follow-up can be evidenced from normal production state, the corrected EXEC\n+  report must use the TASK packet\u0027s `NEEDS_HUMAN` route.\n+\n+## Re-Verification Gates\n+\n+The Executor MUST re-run these gates after the corrections:\n+\n+- `git status --short --untracked-files=no` before and after correction.\n+  Expected: no tracked changes introduced by the Executor.\n+- Read the TASK packet, prior EXEC report, and this CORRECT packet.\n+- Read `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs` and verify the\n+  `SetTimeScale`, `EditorShell::set_time_scale`, and no-op short-circuit\n+  evidence used in the corrected Q2/Q3/Q5 answer.\n+- Read `crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs` and verify\n+  `CompoundAction` plus `impl Action for CompoundAction` are reflected in the\n+  corrected Q1/source inventory.\n+- Search the audited production roots for production callers that can set\n+  `TimeScale` non-default before a proposed reset binding, and record the exact\n+  search mechanism used. If none exist, do not keep `Ctrl+0` reset as the\n+  selected implementation task.\n+- Search the audited production roots for `impl Action` and classify each\n+  production implementation as eligible, rejected, or infrastructure.\n+- Do not run local cargo commands, tests, formatters, architecture lints,\n+  benchmarks, doctests, cargo-deny, source generation, docs generation, or\n+  `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` as part of this audit correction. The orchestrator\n+  verification gate will run after execution.\n+\n+## Halt Conditions (Updated if Any)\n+\n+Unchanged from Task Packet, with this clarification: if the corrected evidence\n+cannot identify a user-visible World-only `CommandBus::submit` follow-up that\n+submits from normal production state, the Executor must route the corrected\n+EXEC report to `NEEDS_HUMAN` rather than preserving the invalid `Ctrl+0`\n+default-reset recommendation.\n+\n+## Planner Notes\n+\n+This correction is intentionally limited to the EXEC report\u0027s audit conclusions\n+and evidence log. It does not authorize implementation, source edits, broader\n+architecture comparison, or Approach B/C reconsideration. The key issue is not\n+whether `SetTimeScale` is World-only; it is whether the named user-visible\n+follow-up would actually call `CommandBus::submit` from normal production state.\n+The corrected report must make that distinction explicit.\n+\n+---\n+\n+HANDOFF_STATUS: COMPLETE\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-132\n+AUTHOR: Planner / OpenAI Codex\n+NEXT_ROLE: EXECUTOR_AI\n+EXIT_CODE: 0\n+\n+---"
