/EXECUTION_REPORT.md` (the EXEC template shape for this packet).\n+21. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `CommandBus|submit_action|command_bus|handle_key_command|set_time_scale|undo_command|redo_command|mark_saved_command` under `editor/rge-editor/src`. Result: zero matches. The binary does not reach the bus.\n+22. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `WindowEvent|KeyboardInput|MouseInput|ElementState|KeyCode|translate_keyboard|handle_button|click|shortcut|toolbar|inspector|slider` under `editor/rge-editor/src`. Result: only `WindowEvent::RedrawRequested` reaches the binary\u0027s `EditorApp::window_event`, which drains the GLB watcher and then forwards to `EditorShell::window_event`. No new bus-bound surfaces in the binary.\n+23. Read `editor/rge-editor/src/main.rs` lines 680вЂ“780 (the `EditorApp::window_event` forwarder + the `main()` head) to confirm the forwarder shape.\n+24. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `insert_resource|resource\\(\\)|Res\u003c|TimeScale|PlayState` under `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle`. Result: `TimeScale` is the only ECS resource the editor-shell production paths read or insert via the bus-routed contract. `PlayState` is an `EditorShell` field, not a `World` resource.\n+25. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `fn set_time_scale|time_scale\\(|\\.set_time_scale\\(` workspace-wide. Result: production definition + accessor in `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/{commands.rs,mod.rs}`; all `set_time_scale(...)` *callers* are in `crates/editor-shell/tests/time_scale_test.rs` (production caller count = 0).\n+26. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `SetTimeScale|SetTime|world\\.insert_resource|world\\.insert\\(|world\\.remove|spawn|despawn` under `crates/editor-actions/src`. Result: confirms the only production `Action` impl is `SetTimeScale` (in `editor-shell::lifecycle::commands`); `editor-actions/src/{action.rs,bus.rs,compound.rs}` only have `#[cfg(test)]` stubs (`InsertVal`, `ReplaceVal`, `InsertMarker`, `Tag`).\n+27. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `egui_consumed|egui_host|InspectorSnapshot|Slider|inspector_snapshot|inspector_widget|TimeScale` under `crates/editor-shell/src`. Result: `EguiHost` is mounted in `lifecycle/mod.rs` + `render_path.rs`; the host exposes `inspector_handoff()` (read-only observation). **No production egui widget reaches `set_time_scale` or `submit_action`.** Inspector is one-way (shell в†’ host), per the inspector module doc.\n+28. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `egui|slider|toolbar_click|button_click` under `editor/rge-editor/src`. Result: zero matches.\n+29. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `inspector_handoff|InspectorHandoff|on_inspector|callback|widget|TabBody::Inspector` under `crates/editor-shell/src`. Result: only `Arc\u003cInspectorHandoff\u003e` is held by `EditorShell` (read-only handoff to the host). No back-channel from host в†’ shell that could carry slider events into `submit_action`.\n+30. `rg` (via Grep tool, `-n`) for `handle_playback_command|EditorPlaybackCommand|toolbar|on_button_press` under `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle`. Result: `EditorPlaybackCommand` (Space/Escape) explicitly bus-free per `playback.rs:5` (`\"No CommandBus involvement; no new ECS state; no toolbar UI.\"`). Toolbar `handle_button` mutates `EditorShell::{state, snapshot, audit}` directly.\n+31. `git status --short` вЂ” post-audit, after writing this EXEC report. Expected result: exactly one new file `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md`, plus the pre-existing untracked TASK packet `.md` / `.meta.json` files that were present before the audit and are documented as such in `Worktree State` below.\n+\n+### Audit-root coverage (each MUST be read-only inspected per Acceptance Criteria)\n+\n+| Root | Inspected? | Evidence |\n+| --- | --- | --- |\n+| `crates/editor-actions/**` | yes | Read `src/{action.rs, bus.rs}` (full); grepped `src/` for `SetTimeScale\\|world\\.insert_resource\\|...`; enumerated remaining `src/{lib,compound,coalesce,undo_stack}.rs` and `tests/*.rs` via `rg --files`. |\n+| `crates/editor-shell/**` | yes | Read `src/{world.rs (head), pick_path.rs, play_toolbar.rs, time_scale.rs, inspector.rs}` and `src/lifecycle/commands.rs` (full); read `src/lifecycle/mod.rs` lines 1100вЂ“1300 and 1600вЂ“1745 (toolbar entry point + window-event branches); grepped `src/` for every CommandBus / egui / inspector identifier listed in command log В§21, В§24, В§27, В§29, В§30. |\n+| `editor/rge-editor/**` | yes | Read `src/main.rs` lines 680вЂ“780 (the `EditorApp::window_event` forwarder); grepped `src/` for every CommandBus + input + inspector + slider identifier. Zero bus references in this binary. |\n+| `crates/editor-state/**` | yes | Read `src/lib.rs` (head) + `src/inspector_snapshot.rs` (full); enumerated other modules (`selection`, `hover`, `face_selection`, `active_tool`, `modal_state`, `drag_drop`) via `rg --files`. Editor-state is non-`World` by doctrine вЂ” `editor-state-ownership` lint pin. |\n+| `kernel/ecs/**` | yes | Read `src/lib.rs` (head); enumerated `src/{world, snapshot, commands, participate, change_detection, archetype, resource, query, entity, component, ...}` via `rg --files`. Confirms `World::{insert_resource, insert, remove, spawn, despawn}` are the World-only mutation primitives accessible from `Action::apply(\u0026mut World)`. |\n+\n+### ISSUE-108 EXEC inspection\n+\n+- File used: `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_2026-05-23_10-08-36+0300.md` (the sole match for `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_*.md`).\n+- Architectural direction adopted for this preflight: **ISSUE-108 Approach A вЂ” keep the existing World-only `Action` surface unchanged**. The bus\u0027s `submit(action: Box\u003cdyn Action\u003e, world: \u0026mut World)` and the trait\u0027s `apply(\u0026self, world: \u0026mut World)` / `revert(\u0026self, world: \u0026mut World)` contracts remain fixed. No widened editor-context `Action`, no `editor-actions` tier-2 promotion, no adapter-layer dual ledger, no Cargo dependency edits, no architecture-lint reshape. Q3 below describes implementation shape for the Q2 pick using Approach A only.\n+\n+### Halt-check outcomes\n+\n+- **HC вЂ” required roots present and inspected.** PASS. All five mandatory audit roots exist on disk, were enumerated via `rg --files`, and the load-bearing files in each were read (see \"Audit-root coverage\" above).\n+- **HC вЂ” ISSUE-108 EXEC readable.** PASS. Single match, full read, Approach A captured.\n+- **HC вЂ” Premise \"first World-only user-visible CommandBus action\" still load-bearing.** PASS (not stale). The only production `Action` impl that reaches `CommandBus::submit` today is `SetTimeScale`, and its sole shell wrapper `EditorShell::set_time_scale(value)` has **zero production callers** (only test callers in `crates/editor-shell/tests/time_scale_test.rs` and `src/lifecycle/tests.rs`). The keyboard branch in `lifecycle/mod.rs:1676вЂ“1723` reaches `CommandBus::{undo, redo, mark_saved}` for `Ctrl+Z`/`Y`/`S` but **never `submit`**. No production user-input path reaches `submit`.\n+- **HC вЂ” at least one eligible World-only user-visible candidate exists.** PASS. See Q1 and Q2 below.\n+\n+## 5-Question World-only CommandBus Action Preflight Answer Block\n+\n+### Q1. Candidate Actions\n+\n+Candidate inventory restricted to user-visible action paths whose mutation target can remain `rge_kernel_ecs::World`-only under the existing `Action::apply(\u0026mut World)` / `revert(\u0026mut World)` and `CommandBus::submit(..., \u0026mut World)` contract. Code evidence cited inline. Every excluded surface from the TASK packet\u0027s exclusion list (editor-state, selection, hover, active tool, `FaceSelection`, `DockState`, egui state, render-path state, asset-reload state, watcher state, `cad-core` `CadGraph`) triggers a rejection.\n+\n+**Eligible (World-only, user-visible, fits the current `Action` contract).**\n+\n+- **E1. `SetTimeScale` driven by a keyboard binding.** Evidence: `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs:149вЂ“241` defines `SetTimeScale` as a production `Action` whose `apply` and `revert` call `world.insert_resource(TimeScale::with_value(...))` вЂ” pure World-resource mutation, byte-identical revert. `EditorShell::set_time_scale(value)` (same file lines 348вЂ“382) already submits it through `CommandBus::submit` via `self.submit_action(Box::new(SetTimeScale::new(from, to)))` against `self.world.kernel_mut()`. The user-visible trigger does not yet exist вЂ” `lifecycle/mod.rs:1676вЂ“1723`\u0027s `KeyboardInput` branch routes only `Ctrl+Z`/`Y`/`S` (Undo/Redo/MarkSaved), `Space`/`Escape` (playback, bus-free), and plain `R` (asset reload, bus-free); no key binding currently calls `self.set_time_scale(...)`. Adding one (e.g. `Ctrl+0` в†’ reset time-scale to `TimeScale::DEFAULT`) is the load-bearing \"first World-only user-visible CommandBus action\" wiring. World-only вњ“; user-visible вњ“; fits current `Action` contract verbatim вњ“; no editor-state, no egui, no CAD touched.\n+\n+**Rejected (touch an excluded mutation surface or are non-user-visible).**\n+\n+- **R1. Mouse left-click face pick** вЂ” `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:1641вЂ“1666` в†’ `crates/editor-shell/src/pick_path.rs:58вЂ“121`. Rejection reason: mutates `self.coord.face_selection: editor_state::FaceSelectionSet` and `self.highlight_index_buffer: Option\u003crge_gfx::IndexBuffer\u003e` (excluded surfaces: `editor-state`, `FaceSelection`, `face_selection`, render-path state). Cannot remain World-only under the current `Action::apply(\u0026mut World)` contract.\n+- **R2. Toolbar `handle_button(ToolbarButtonId)` вЂ” Play / Pause / Stop / Step / FrameStep.** Evidence: `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:1126вЂ“1180` and `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/playback.rs:5` (\"No CommandBus involvement; no new ECS state; no toolbar UI.\"). Rejection reason: mutates `EditorShell::{state: PlayState, snapshot: Option\u003cWorldSnapshot\u003e, audit: AuditLedger}` (editor coordination + lifecycle, not `World` resources); `Step` and `FrameStep` advance `EditorShell::tick_count`. None of these are `World` mutations under the current contract; routing them would require either widening `Action` (Approach B вЂ” fixed-excluded) or an adapter (Approach C вЂ” fixed-excluded). Bus-free is the documented design.\n+- **R3. `EditorPlaybackCommand` (`Space` / `Escape`).** Evidence: `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/playback.rs:5` and `lifecycle/mod.rs:1706вЂ“1709`. Rejection reason: identical surface to R2 (`Space` в†’ `TogglePlay`, `Escape` в†’ `Stop`); explicitly bus-free.\n+- **R4. Plain `R` вЂ” asset hot-reload.** Evidence: `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:1710вЂ“1721`, `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/asset_reload.rs:29вЂ“119`. Rejection reason: mutates render-path state (mesh / material reload), watcher state, and `EditorShell::cad_graph` (excluded surfaces: render-path state, asset-reload state, watcher state, `cad-core` `CadGraph`).\n+- **R5. GLB watcher tick (`EditorApp::window_event` drain in `editor/rge-editor/src/main.rs:704вЂ“724`).** Rejection reason: not a user action (it is a binary-loop drain that piggybacks `WindowEvent::RedrawRequested`); even if classified user-visible, it mutates watcher + render-path state. Excluded twice over.\n+- **R6. `WindowEvent::CursorMoved` + `WindowEvent::ModifiersChanged`.** Evidence: `lifecycle/mod.rs:1634вЂ“1640, 1668вЂ“1675`. Rejection reason: bookkeeping only (`self.cursor_pos`, `self.modifiers`) вЂ” no user-visible mutation, no undo semantics, not a CommandBus candidate.\n+- **R7. egui inspector / dock interactions (future \"slider\" path).** Evidence: `crates/editor-shell/src/inspector.rs` is a re-export of the read-only `InspectorSnapshot` aggregator (`crates/editor-state/src/inspector_snapshot.rs:1вЂ“117`); `EditorShell` only **publishes** an `Arc\u003cInspectorHandoff\u003e` to the host (`lifecycle/mod.rs:533вЂ“554`, `render_path.rs:289вЂ“298`). Rejection reason for *now*: no production back-channel exists from `EguiHost`/`InspectorTabBody` back to `EditorShell::set_time_scale` or `submit_action` (the inspector module doc-comment explicitly defers the consumer side to the `editor-ui` crate, \"the future consumer, via the `widgets::inspector` render fn\"). Wiring a back-channel **also** introduces egui-state / `DockState` / `InspectorHandoff` coupling, which the TASK packet\u0027s exclusion list rejects (\"egui state\", \"`DockState`\"). Therefore the egui-slider variant is rejected for this preflight even though the **underlying** mutation (`TimeScale` resource via `SetTimeScale::apply`) is World-only вЂ” the *path* is not, because it would have to traverse egui state to deliver the value.\n+- **R8. Test-only paths.** All `crates/editor-shell/tests/*.rs` and `crates/editor-actions/tests/*.rs` files (including `keyboard_command_bus_round_trip.rs`, `time_scale_test.rs`, `inspector_snapshot_smoke.rs`, `editor_coord_face_selection.rs`, `compound_atomic.rs`, etc.) and the `#[cfg(test)]` stubs `InsertVal` / `ReplaceVal` / `InsertMarker` / `Tag` in `editor-actions/src/{action,bus,compound}.rs`. Rejection reason: per the TASK packet, \"tests, stubs, inactive helpers\" are not eligible candidates.\n+\n+### Q2. Smallest Pick\n+\n+**Bind `Ctrl+0` to reset the `TimeScale` resource to `TimeScale::DEFAULT` (1.0) via the existing `SetTimeScale` action and `CommandBus::submit`.**\n+\n+Rationale (smallest among the eligible set):\n+- The production `Action` impl already exists (`SetTimeScale`, fully implemented with `apply` / `revert` / `payload` / `merge`).\n+- The shell wrapper already exists (`EditorShell::set_time_scale(value: f32)`), with no-op short-circuit, dual-ledger audit event, and bus error swallowing.\n+- The keyboard branch (`lifecycle/mod.rs:1676вЂ“1723`) already exists, already gates on `!egui_consumed`, and already dispatches modifier-bound `EditorKeyCommand`s.\n+- The only missing piece is one new enum variant + one match arm in `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press` + one match arm in `EditorShell::handle_key_command`. No new types, no new crate, no new file, no Cargo edit, no trait widening, no `editor-actions` change at all.\n+- The mutation surface is exactly one `World` resource (`TimeScale`), and `SetTimeScale::apply` / `revert` operate on `\u0026mut rge_kernel_ecs::World` only. No editor-state, no egui, no CAD, no asset reload, no watcher.\n+\n+Alternative-eligible-candidate-but-larger: a more elaborate slider-style binding (e.g. `Ctrl+]` / `Ctrl+[` to step time-scale up/down by a fixed factor). Two key bindings, two match arms, two helper \"from/to\" computations. Strictly larger. Rejected as \"smallest\" for that reason; remains an Approach A-compatible future direction.\n+\n+### Q3. Implementation Shape\n+\n+Approach A only вЂ” World-only `Action` surface, no `editor-actions` dependency promotion, no editor-wide command context, no adapter-layer dual ledger, no Cargo changes, no mutation outside `rge_kernel_ecs::World` plus the already-established dual-ledger audit + dirty-flag behavior that `EditorShell::set_time_scale` already encodes today.\n+\n+Concrete shape:\n+1. **Extend `EditorKeyCommand`** in `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs` with one new variant вЂ” name it `ResetTimeScale` (single tuple-unit variant; carries no payload because the target value is the constant `TimeScale::DEFAULT`). This is additive on a non-exhaustive-style closed enum whose own doc-comment explicitly endorses extension (\"Future editor keybinds (Play/Stop, selection clear, tool switch) extend this enum rather than growing parallel command channels\").\n+2. **Extend `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press`** in the same file (lines ~101вЂ“113) with one arm that maps `(KeyCode::Digit0, ctrl=true, shift=false)` to `Some(Self::ResetTimeScale)`. The existing `!ctrl || shift` early-return already filters bad modifier combinations; the new arm is one literal pattern match. No new trait import, no new dependency. (Verify the exact `KeyCode` variant name for the `0` key in `rge_input` during the implementation task; treat `KeyCode::Digit0` as the working name pending grep.)\n+3. **Extend `EditorShell::handle_key_command`** in the same file (lines 307вЂ“327) with one match arm that calls `self.set_time_scale(TimeScale::DEFAULT)`. The existing `set_time_scale` method already (a) captures `from`, (b) clamps `to`, (c) skips no-ops via `f32::EPSILON`, (d) builds `Box\u003cSetTimeScale\u003e`, (e) submits through `self.command_bus.submit(action, self.world.kernel_mut())`, (f) records a `TimeScaleChanged` audit event on the shell\u0027s own ring buffer. All five lines of supporting logic already exist; the new arm is a single call.\n+4. **No other source edits.** `crates/editor-actions/**` is not touched вЂ” `Action`, `CommandBus`, `BusEntry`, `BusError`, `ActionResult`, `ActionId`, `MergeOutcome` all remain on their current `\u0026mut rge_kernel_ecs::World` surface. `crates/editor-state/**` is not touched. `editor/rge-editor/**` is not touched (the binary already forwards `WindowEvent` to the shell; the new binding falls out for free). `kernel/ecs/**` is not touched.\n+5. **No Cargo, no manifest, no lockfile, no feature flag, no workspace, no lint-config, no doctrine edit.** All needed dependencies (`rge_editor_actions`, `rge_input`, `rge_kernel_ecs`) are already in `crates/editor-shell/Cargo.toml`.\n+6. **Mutation envelope is World-only.** The bus call advances `rge_kernel_ecs::World`\u0027s `TimeScale` resource via `World::insert_resource(TimeScale::with_value(TimeScale::DEFAULT))`. The bus\u0027s internal audit ledger records one `EventKind::Action` event (with `SetTimeScale::payload()` bytes = `TimeScale::DEFAULT.to_le_bytes()`). The undo-stack cursor advances by one. `is_dirty()` flips to `true` (was `false` immediately after `mark_saved`). The shell\u0027s own `audit.record(AuditEvent::TimeScaleChanged { from, to })` runs once. Every effect is either a `World` mutation or an already-established side effect of the existing `set_time_scale` method вЂ” no new authority.\n+7. **Coalesce semantics already correct.** `SetTimeScale::id()` returns the constant `\"set-time-scale\"`; pressing `Ctrl+0` twice within 500 ms coalesces into one stack entry whose `revert` restores the pre-`Ctrl+0` `from`. No additional design required.\n+8. **No-op semantics already correct.** If the user presses `Ctrl+0` while `TimeScale` is already at `DEFAULT`, the existing `(to - from).abs() \u003c f32::EPSILON` short-circuit in `set_time_scale` skips the bus submit AND the shell-side audit append. No phantom undo entry, no spurious `is_dirty` flip.\n+\n+### Q4. Verification Plan\n+\n+Read-only evidence to gather **before** the future implementation task fires (so the implementation can land in one focused dispatch):\n+\n+- Confirm the exact `rge_input::KeyCode` variant name for the `0` key (`KeyCode::Digit0` vs `KeyCode::Key0` vs a numeric-row alias) by grepping `crates/input/src/**` (or wherever `rge_input` lives). The TASK packet for the implementation must encode the verified variant name; otherwise the implementor will guess.\n+- Confirm there is no existing `Ctrl+0` binding that the new variant would shadow. Search the editor-shell + editor binary for `KeyCode::Digit0` / `KeyCode::Key0` / `Ctrl+0` references. None expected based on this preflight\u0027s reads, but the implementation task should re-verify.\n+- Confirm `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press` has not been moved or renamed in the interim. Re-read `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs` lines 75вЂ“113 immediately before implementing.\n+\n+Verification gates the future implementation dispatch MUST run (this preflight runs **none** of them):\n+\n+- `cargo build -p rge-editor-shell` вЂ” confirms the new variant + match arms compile.\n+- `cargo +nightly fmt --check -p rge-editor-shell` (or workspace fmt-check per local convention).\n+- `cargo clippy -p rge-editor-shell --all-targets -- -D warnings`.\n+- `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test keyboard_command_bus_round_trip` вЂ” the existing `Ctrl+Z`/`Y`/`S` round-trip test pattern is the natural extension point for a `Ctrl+0` round-trip case.\n+- `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test time_scale_test` вЂ” the existing `set_time_scale_routes_through_bus_and_undo_redo_round_trips` test already exercises the bus path; the new keyboard-driven case should reuse the same headless harness via `EditorShell::handle_key_command(EditorKeyCommand::ResetTimeScale)` (the doc-comment already states \"Public so headless tests can drive the bus without synthesizing winit `KeyEvent`s\").\n+- `cargo test --workspace --no-fail-fast` вЂ” workspace regression sweep.\n+- `cargo run -q -p rge-tool-architecture-lints -- all` вЂ” confirms no architecture-lint posture changes (no new `forbidden-dep` violations, no `editor-state-ownership` violations, no `editor-actions` tier shift).\n+- `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` вЂ” the canonical dispatch verification gate.\n+\n+Likely focused tests the future implementation should add (read-only opinion; the implementor decides):\n+\n+- One test pinning `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press(KeyCode::Digit0, ctrl=true, shift=false) == Some(EditorKeyCommand::ResetTimeScale)`, and that `shift=true` / `ctrl=false` return `None` (existing modifier-gate invariant preserved).\n+- One test that builds an `EditorShell`, sets `TimeScale` to some non-default value via the existing test path, calls `shell.handle_key_command(EditorKeyCommand::ResetTimeScale)`, and asserts the resource reads `TimeScale::DEFAULT` plus the bus\u0027s `stack().cursor()` advanced by 1 plus `command_bus().is_dirty() == true`.\n+- One test that asserts `shell.undo_command()` immediately after a `ResetTimeScale` press restores the pre-press `TimeScale` value byte-identically.\n+- One test that asserts pressing `Ctrl+0` while already at `DEFAULT` is a no-op (no cursor advance, no dirty flip, no audit-event append) вЂ” this exercises the existing no-op short-circuit on a new caller.\n+\n+### Q5. Follow-Up Task Surface\n+\n+Exactly one smallest follow-up implementation task. Bound it like this when the Planner writes the TASK packet:\n+\n+- **Goal.** Wire `Ctrl+0` to reset `TimeScale` to `TimeScale::DEFAULT` through `CommandBus::submit(SetTimeScale, World)`. Achieve \"first user-visible CommandBus action that calls `submit`\" by extending the existing `EditorKeyCommand` enum and the existing `EditorShell::handle_key_command` dispatch.\n+- **MAY edit (allowed file surface).**\n+  - `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs` вЂ” add one `EditorKeyCommand::ResetTimeScale` variant; add one arm to `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press`; add one arm to `EditorShell::handle_key_command` that calls `self.set_time_scale(TimeScale::DEFAULT)`.\n+  - `crates/editor-shell/tests/keyboard_command_bus_round_trip.rs` and/or `crates/editor-shell/tests/time_scale_test.rs` вЂ” extend with the focused-test cases from Q4. New file allowed only if extending the existing ones is structurally awkward; prefer extension.\n+- **MUST NOT touch.**\n+  - `crates/editor-actions/**` вЂ” no trait widening, no bus signature change, no payload format change, no `BusEntry` variant addition, no `ActionId` rename.\n+  - `crates/editor-state/**` вЂ” no coordination-category change, no editor-state-ownership lint change.\n+  - `editor/rge-editor/**` вЂ” the binary forwards `WindowEvent` to the shell unchanged; do not touch `main.rs`.\n+  - `kernel/ecs/**` вЂ” no `World` API change, no new `Resource` type, no kernel-level edits.\n+  - Any `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, workspace manifest, feature flag, or dependency declaration.\n+  - Any architecture-lint configuration, doctrine document, ADR, `plans/` markdown, `.gitignore`, or repository-metadata file.\n+  - Any existing handoff packet (including this EXEC).\n+  - Any GitHub issue, label, PR, branch, commit, or remote state.\n+  - `crates/editor-shell/src/{pick_path.rs, audit.rs, snapshot.rs, render_path.rs, render_input.rs, render_frame_e2e_perf.rs, viewport.rs, coord.rs, camera.rs, play_state.rs, play_toolbar.rs, time_scale.rs, world.rs, inspector.rs, visual_smoke.rs, visual_test_harness.rs, lifecycle/playback.rs, lifecycle/asset_reload.rs, lifecycle/mod.rs}` вЂ” none of these need to change for `Ctrl+0` reset. (`lifecycle/mod.rs`\u0027s `KeyboardInput` branch already dispatches `EditorKeyCommand` and falls through correctly; the new variant flows for free.)\n+- **Verification gates.** Run, in order: `cargo build -p rge-editor-shell`; `cargo +nightly fmt --check -p rge-editor-shell` (or local workspace equivalent); `cargo clippy -p rge-editor-shell --all-targets -- -D warnings`; `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test keyboard_command_bus_round_trip`; `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test time_scale_test`; `cargo test --workspace --no-fail-fast`; `cargo run -q -p rge-tool-architecture-lints -- all`; `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1`. All gates must pass before close-out.\n+- **Halt conditions.** Halt and request fresh guidance if any of the following occur:\n+  - The `rge_input::KeyCode` variant for `0` cannot be confirmed by grep, OR an existing `Ctrl+0` binding is discovered that would be shadowed.\n+  - `EditorKeyCommand`, `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press`, or `EditorShell::handle_key_command` have been moved, renamed, or restructured since this preflight (re-read before implementing).\n+  - Implementing the binding requires editing `crates/editor-actions/src/{action.rs, bus.rs, lib.rs, compound.rs}` or touching the `Action`-trait signature, the `CommandBus::submit` signature, or any non-`World` mutation surface.\n+  - Any verification gate fails for a reason other than the new test case being incomplete (e.g. architecture lint flips, `forbidden-dep` violation, workspace test regression).\n+  - A new Cargo dependency, feature flag, or workspace edit becomes necessary.\n+  - The implementation cannot be completed without widening `EditorKeyCommand` beyond one new variant + one new map arm + one new dispatch arm, indicating a scope miscarve.\n+  - The audit-only conclusions of this preflight are contradicted by current code state (e.g. a production caller of `set_time_scale` has appeared in the interim вЂ” the \"first action\" premise would be stale).\n+\n+## Deviations from Task Packet\n+\n+None вЂ” execution stayed strictly within the Task Packet scope. No source, tests, docs, manifests, Cargo files, scripts, schemas, status files, workflows, lint configs, doctrine documents, existing packets, or GitHub state were edited or added; only this single EXEC report was created. No cargo / test / formatter / architecture-lint / benchmark / doctest / `cargo-deny` / `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` / source-generation / docs-generation command was run.\n+\n+## Open Questions for Reviewer\n+\n+- The `rge_input::KeyCode::Digit0` variant name is used in Q3 / Q5 as a working hypothesis. The current preflight did not read `crates/input/**` (it is not one of the five mandatory audit roots). The Q5 halt condition \"the `rge_input::KeyCode` variant for `0` cannot be confirmed by grep\" explicitly defers this to the implementation dispatch. If the Reviewer prefers, a one-line grep on `crates/input/src/*` for `Digit0|Key0` could be added in a follow-up, but doing so now would broaden the audit beyond its stated roots; this preflight has chosen the narrower posture.\n+- Q5 names `Ctrl+0` as the smallest binding. If the project has a preference for a different smallest binding (e.g. a single increment `Ctrl+]` rather than a reset-to-default `Ctrl+0`), the human arbiter can substitute one for the other in the follow-up TASK packet without changing the Approach-A implementation shape. The trade-off (single vs two arms) is documented in Q2.\n+- The audit deliberately did not inspect `crates/cad-core/**`, `crates/cad-projection/**`, `crates/editor-egui-host/**`, or any `editor-ui` crate. They were inside ISSUE-108\u0027s wider preflight surface but are outside ISSUE-132\u0027s narrower five-root scope, and none of them are needed to answer Q1вЂ“Q5 under the World-only / Approach-A constraint.\n+\n+## Worktree State\n+\n+- Tracked files: clean.\n+- Untracked items: `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_TASK_2026-05-23_22-32-44+0300.md` and `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_TASK_2026-05-23_22-32-44+0300.meta.json` (pre-existing TASK packet, present before the audit and documented as such); `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md` (this report; the only Executor-created change). The EXEC sidecar will be created by `new-handoff.ps1 -Finalize`.\n+- Branch: `ai-dispatch/ISSUE-132`.\n+- Last commit: `cb63077` chore(dispatch): seed task #24 World-only CommandBus action preflight.\n+\n+---\n+\n+HANDOFF_STATUS: COMPLETE\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-132\n+AUTHOR: Executor / Claude\n+NEXT_ROLE: REVIEWER_AI\n+EXIT_CODE: 0\n+\n+---"
