        "patch":  "@@ -0,0 +1,813 @@\n+# Execution Report\n+\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-132\n+AUTHOR: Executor / Claude\n+TIMESTAMP: 2026-05-23_23-01-08+0300\n+RELATED_FILES:\n+- ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_23-01-08+0300.md вЂ” corrected read-only World-only CommandBus action preflight report (this file).\n+STATUS: AWAITING_REVIEW\n+\n+## Task Packet Reference\n+\n+`ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_TASK_2026-05-23_22-32-44+0300.md`\n+\n+## Correction Packet Reference\n+\n+`ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_CORRECT_2026-05-23_22-55-20+0300.md` вЂ” addresses three\n+Codex control-review findings against the prior EXEC report\n+(`ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md`):\n+\n+1. The `Ctrl+0` reset-to-default pick is invalid because no production caller\n+   makes `TimeScale` non-default, so the proposed binding would always hit the\n+   `EditorShell::set_time_scale` no-op short-circuit and never call\n+   `CommandBus::submit`. Q2/Q3/Q5 must be revised to a genuinely non-noop,\n+   user-visible, World-only submit path or routed to `NEEDS_HUMAN`.\n+2. The production `Action` inventory must include `CompoundAction` in\n+   `crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs`, classified accurately, and must not\n+   claim `SetTimeScale` is the only production `Action` impl.\n+3. The command log must accurately separate shell `rg` from agent-tool\n+   (Claude Grep/Glob) searches and may use PowerShell fallbacks where shell\n+   `rg` is unavailable. Do not claim `command -v rg` / shell `rg` / `rg --files`\n+   ran unless they actually ran in the Executor\u0027s shell.\n+\n+This corrected EXEC report addresses all three findings. The prior TASK,\n+prior EXEC, and CORRECT packets are not modified.\n+\n+## Pre-Execution Review Consumed\n+\n+No pre-execution review issued for this dispatch. The CORRECT packet referenced\n+above is consumed in full; the Executor concurs with all three approved\n+corrections.\n+\n+## What I Changed\n+\n+### Source\n+\n+- None. This is a read-only audit-correction round. No source, tests, docs,\n+  manifests, Cargo files, scripts, schemas, doctrine, ADRs, workflows, status\n+  files, lint configurations, prior handoff packets, GitHub state, or any\n+  other repository file was edited or created, with the sole exception of this\n+  single corrected `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_*.md` report. The prior TASK,\n+  prior EXEC, and CORRECT packets are preserved verbatim per the CORRECT\n+  packet\u0027s \"must not be rewritten\" instruction.\n+\n+### Tests\n+\n+- None added. No test code was edited.\n+\n+### Docs\n+\n+- None added outside this EXEC report.\n+\n+## Per-File Summary\n+\n+Single new file: this corrected EXEC report. No other tracked or untracked\n+changes introduced by the Executor in this correction round.\n+\n+## Verification Results\n+\n+This dispatch is audit-only. **No local cargo commands, tests, formatters,\n+architecture lints, benchmarks, doctests, `cargo-deny`, source generation,\n+docs generation, or `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` were run**, per the TASK packet\u0027s\n+`Constraints / Non-Goals`, the TASK packet\u0027s `Verification Gates`, and the\n+CORRECT packet\u0027s re-verification gates. The gates below are read/search/status\n+only.\n+\n+### Tooling vocabulary (separates shell from agent search)\n+\n+The CORRECT packet finding #3 requires accurate separation of the two distinct\n+search mechanisms available in this dispatch:\n+\n+- **Shell commands** вЂ” invoked through the Executor\u0027s Bash tool, run by the\n+  host OS shell. `rg`, `git`, `command -v` belong here. Each entry below\n+  marked `(shell: \u003ctool\u003e)` was actually run by the OS shell in this round.\n+- **Agent search tooling** вЂ” Claude\u0027s Grep tool (a ripgrep wrapper inside the\n+  agent harness, NOT a shell invocation) and Claude\u0027s Glob tool (a filesystem\n+  glob inside the agent harness). Each entry below marked `(agent: Grep)` or\n+  `(agent: Glob)` is an agent-tool search and does NOT prove shell-level\n+  `rg` ran for that step.\n+\n+`command -v rg` was actually run as a shell command in this correction round\n+(see CL-2 below) and confirms ripgrep 15.1.0 is on the Executor\u0027s `PATH`\n+at `/c/Users/halil/AppData/Roaming/npm/node_modules/@openai/codex/node_modules/@openai/codex-win32-x64/vendor/x86_64-pc-windows-msvc/path/rg`.\n+No PowerShell `Get-ChildItem -Recurse` / `Select-String` fallback was therefore\n+required in this round. The Codex control reviewer observed `rg` unavailable\n+in their separate environment вЂ” that observation is correct for the\n+reviewer\u0027s environment, but it does not retro-invalidate the prior EXEC\u0027s\n+log; the prior EXEC was simply not explicit about which searches were\n+shell-`rg` vs agent-Grep. This corrected report makes that split explicit.\n+\n+### Command Log (read / search / status only)\n+\n+Below, every entry is tagged with `(shell: ...)` for an OS-shell invocation\n+or `(agent: ...)` for an agent-harness search tool. Read entries with no\n+search are tagged `(agent: Read)` for the Claude Read tool. The log covers\n+the correction round; the prior EXEC report\u0027s command log (in\n+`ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md`, command-log В§1вЂ“В§31)\n+is preserved unchanged in that file and is incorporated here by reference.\n+The corrections to that prior log are:\n+\n+- Prior CL В§1 вЂ” `git status --short --untracked-files=no` вЂ” WAS shell. Re-run\n+  in this round at CL-1 below. Output: empty.\n+- Prior CL В§3 вЂ” `git log -1 --pretty=\u0027%h %s\u0027` вЂ” WAS shell. Result still\n+  applies: `cb63077 chore(dispatch): seed task #24 World-only CommandBus\n+  action preflight`.\n+- Prior CL В§4 вЂ” `Glob ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_*.md` вЂ” was the Claude Glob\n+  agent tool, NOT shell `glob`. Re-label as `(agent: Glob)`. Result still\n+  applies: one match (`ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_2026-05-23_10-08-36+0300.md`).\n+- Prior CL В§6 вЂ” claim that `rg --files crates/...` and `command -v rg` were\n+  shel