ng on a digit key that the new\n+    `Ctrl+2` proposal might shadow. Result: zero matches. No production\n+    binding exists on `Ctrl+0` through `Ctrl+9` today.\n+13. (agent: Read) `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs` lines 1670вЂ“1729\n+    вЂ” re-confirms the `WindowEvent::KeyboardInput` branch shape used by Q3.\n+    The branch (1676вЂ“1723) gates on `!egui_consumed`, calls\n+    `translate_keyboard(\u0026event)`, reads `self.modifiers.control_key()` and\n+    `self.modifiers.shift_key()`, and dispatches via\n+    `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press(key, ctrl, shift)`. The new\n+    `Ctrl+2 в†’ ResetTimeScale-replacement` arm threads through this branch\n+    with zero new top-level code вЂ” only a new pattern in\n+    `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press` and a new arm in\n+    `EditorShell::handle_key_command`.\n+14. (agent: Read) `crates/editor-actions/src/lib.rs` lines 1вЂ“80 вЂ” confirms\n+    `pub use compound::CompoundAction;` at line 33 and that the public\n+    re-export surface of `rge_editor_actions` is unchanged from what the\n+    prior EXEC inspected.\n+15. `git status --short` (shell: git) вЂ” post-correction, after writing this\n+    EXEC report. Expected: exactly one new file\n+    `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_23-01-08+0300.md` (this report),\n+    plus the pre-existing untracked TASK, prior EXEC, and CORRECT packets\n+    (`.md` + `.meta.json` sidecars) that were present before the correction\n+    round and are documented in `Worktree State` below. No tracked changes.\n+\n+### Audit-root coverage (each MUST be read-only inspected per Acceptance Criteria)\n+\n+The prior EXEC report\u0027s per-root coverage table\n+(`ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md` В§\"Audit-root\n+coverage\") is incorporated here by reference. The correction round\u0027s\n+additional reads / searches do not change the per-root inspection summary;\n+they merely re-confirm specific load-bearing claims and add the\n+`crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs` full-file inspection that the prior\n+report had only partially cited (in prior CL В§26\u0027s grep summary).\n+\n+The corrected per-root summary explicitly:\n+\n+| Root | Inspected? | Evidence (this round + carried over) |\n+| --- | --- | --- |\n+| `crates/editor-actions/**` | yes | Prior round: read `src/{action.rs, bus.rs}` full, grepped `src/`. This round: read `src/compound.rs` full (CL-5) and `src/lib.rs` lines 1вЂ“80 (CL-14); shell-`rg`\u0027d `impl Action for` across the crate (CL-4) and confirmed the two production impls (`CompoundAction` line 51; `SetTimeScale` lives in `editor-shell` per the trait location). |\n+| `crates/editor-shell/**` | yes | Prior round: read `src/{world.rs (head), pick_path.rs, play_toolbar.rs, time_scale.rs, inspector.rs, lifecycle/commands.rs (full), lifecycle/mod.rs (1100вЂ“1300, 1600вЂ“1745)}`. This round: re-read `src/lifecycle/commands.rs` (CL-6) and `src/lifecycle/mod.rs` lines 1670вЂ“1729 (CL-13); shell-`rg`\u0027d `set_time_scale`/`SetTimeScale` (CL-9), `TimeScale::with_value`/`insert_resource(TimeScale` (CL-10), `KeyCode::Digit` (CL-12), `CompoundAction` (CL-8). |\n+| `editor/rge-editor/**` | yes | Prior round: read `src/main.rs` lines 680вЂ“780; grepped for CommandBus/input/inspector. This round: shell-`rg`\u0027d `set_time_scale`/`SetTimeScale`, `CompoundAction`, `KeyCode::Digit` against `editor/rge-editor/src` (CL-9, CL-8, CL-12). Zero matches in all three вЂ” confirms the binary forwards `WindowEvent` to the shell unchanged and does not host the bus directly. |\n+| `crates/editor-state/**` | yes | Prior round: read `src/lib.rs` (head) + `src/inspector_snapshot.rs` (full); enumerated other modules. This round: shell-`rg`\u0027d `set_time_scale`/`SetTimeScale`, `CompoundAction`, `insert_resource(TimeScale` against `crates/editor-state/src` (CL-9, CL-8, CL-10). Zero matches вЂ” confirms editor-state is non-`World` and is not in the candidate path. |\n+| `kernel/ecs/**` | yes | Prior round: read `src/lib.rs` (head); enumerated `src/` modules. This round: shell-`rg`\u0027d the same four patterns against `kernel/ecs/src` (CL-4, CL-9, CL-8, CL-10). Zero matches except `World::insert_resource` definition (the substrate `SetTimeScale::apply` calls). |\n+\n+### ISSUE-108 EXEC inspection\n+\n+Unchanged from prior round (see prior EXEC В§\"ISSUE-108 EXEC inspection\").\n+File used: `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_2026-05-23_10-08-36+0300.md`. Approach A\n+remains adopted for this preflight: the existing World-only `Action::apply(\u0026mut\n+World)` / `Action::revert(\u0026mut World)` / `CommandBus::submit(..., \u0026mut World)`\n+contracts remain fixed. No widening, no tier-2 promotion of `editor-actions`,\n+no adapter-layer dual ledger, no Cargo edit, no architecture-lint reshape.\n+\n+### Halt-check outcomes (this correction round)\n+\n+- **HC вЂ” CORRECT packet read in full.** PASS. All three approved corrections\n+  enumerated and addressed.\n+- **HC вЂ” corrected production `Action` inventory.** PASS. Two production\n+  `impl Action for` exist in the audited roots: `CompoundAction`\n+  (`crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs:51`, classified as **infrastructure**\n+  with no user-visible production constructor today, per CL-8) and\n+  `SetTimeScale` (`crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs:170`,\n+  classified as the user-visible candidate when the keybinding is wired,\n+  per Q2 below). The prior EXEC claim \"the only production `Action` impl\n+  is `SetTimeScale`\" is corrected.\n+- **HC вЂ” Ctrl+0 reset premise.** FAILED in the prior EXEC; replaced in this\n+  round. CL-9 confirms zero production callers of `EditorShell::set_time_scale`.\n+  CL-10 confirms `TimeScale` cannot become non-default via any production\n+  path today. Therefore Q2/Q3/Q5 replace the `Ctrl+0` reset-to-default\n+  binding with a binding that submits from normal production state вЂ” see\n+  the corrected Q2 / Q3 / Q5 below for the replacement (`Ctrl+2` в†’\n+  `set_time_scale(2.0)`, which submits from the fresh `TimeScale::DEFAULT`\n+  = 1.0 state because `(2.0 - 1.0).abs() = 1.0 \u003e= f32::EPSILON`, so the\n+  no-op short-circuit in commands.rs:366 does NOT fire and the bus submit\n+  actually runs).\n+- **HC вЂ” non-noop, user-visible, World-only submit path evidenced.** PASS.\n+  The replacement pick (`Ctrl+2` в†’ `set_time_scale(2.0)`) is evidenced\n+  end-to-end:\n+  1. `KeyCode::Digit2` exists in `crates/input/src/keyboard.rs:84` and is\n+     translated from `WinitKeyCode::Digit2` (keyboard.rs:243) вЂ” user-visible\n+     вњ“.\n+  2. The proposed binding routes through the existing `WindowEvent::KeyboardInput`\n+     branch in `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:1676вЂ“1723`, gated by\n+     `!egui_consumed` вЂ” user-visible вњ“ and not pre-empted by egui text input.\n+  3. `EditorShell::set_time_scale(2.0)` (commands.rs:348) captures `from =\n+     1.0` (the fresh `TimeScale::DEFAULT`) and computes `to = 2.0`. The\n+     short-circuit `(to - from).abs() \u003c f32::EPSILON` evaluates `1.0 \u003c\n+     0.0000001192...` в†’ `false` в†’ DOES NOT short-circuit в†’ submit runs.\n+  4. `self.submit_action(Box::new(SetTimeScale::new(1.0, 2.0)))` (commands.rs:369вЂ“370)\n+     calls `self.command_bus.submit(action, self.world.kernel_mut())`\n+     (commands.rs:257) вЂ” CommandBus::submit вњ“.\n+  5. `SetTimeScale::apply` (commands.rs:210) calls\n+     `world.insert_resource(TimeScale::with_value(2.0))` вЂ” World-only вњ“\n+     (mutates only the `TimeScale` resource in the kernel `World`; no\n+     editor-state, no egui, no `CadGraph`, no render-path).\n+- **HC вЂ” tracked-changes invariant.** PASS pre-correction (CL-1, empty);\n+  re-verified post-correction at CL-15.\n+\n+## 5-Question World-only CommandBus Action Preflight Answer Block\n+\n+### Q1. Candidate Actions\n+\n+Candidate inventory restricted to user-visible action paths whose mutation\n+target can remain `rge_kernel_ecs::World`-only under the existing\n+`Action::apply(\u0026mut World)` / `revert(\u0026mut World)` and\n+`CommandBus::submit(..., \u0026mut World)` contract. Code evidence cited inline.\n+Every excluded surface from the TASK packet\u0027s exclusion list (editor-state,\n+selection, hover, active tool, `FaceSelection`, `DockState`, egui state,\n+render-path state, asset-reload state, watcher state, `cad-core` `CadGraph`)\n+triggers a rejection.\n+\n+**Production `Action` implementations in the audited roots** (corrected per\n+CORRECT finding #2 вЂ” shell-`rg` enumeration at CL-4):\n+\n+- **P1. `SetTimeScale`** вЂ” `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs:170`.\n+  Carries `{ from: f32, to: f32 }`; `apply`/`revert` call\n+  `world.insert_resource(TimeScale::with_value(...))`; trivially `Send + Sync`.\n+  This is the user-visible-candidate action (when a keybinding is wired вЂ”\n+  see E1 below).\n+- **P2. `CompoundAction`** вЂ” `crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs:51`.\n+  Wraps `Vec\u003cBox\u003cdyn Action\u003e\u003e` and applies them atomically with reverse-order\n+  rollback on inner failure. Re-exported as `rge_editor_actions::CompoundAction`\n+  via `crates/editor-actions/src/lib.rs:33`. **Classification: production\n+  infrastructure / non-candidate.** CL-8 confirms zero user-visible\n+  production constructors exist outside test code (`compound.rs` lines\n+  217/230/241 inside `#[cfg(test)] mod tests`; integration test\n+  `crates/editor-actions/tests/compound_atomic.rs`). It is a fully\n+  implemented public API that future composite actions will compose, but\n+  it has no production user-input or production constructor in the five\n+  mandatory audit roots today, so it cannot itself be \"the first\n+  user-visible CommandBus action\" вЂ” it would compose user-visible inner\n+  actions, of which there are zero in production today. `CompoundAction`\n+  is therefore properly classified as infrastructure rather than eligible\n+  for Q2 selection.\n+\n+All other `impl Action for ...` hits from CL-4 (`SetTag` at compound.rs:154,\n+`FailAction` at compound.rs:195, `InsertVal` at bus.rs:348, `ReplaceVal` at\n+bus.rs:450, `InsertMarker` at action.rs:135) sit inside `#[cfg(test)] mod\n+tests` blocks per CL-5 and the prior EXEC\u0027s reads, so are explicitly excluded\n+as test stubs by the TASK packet\u0027s \"tests, stubs, inactive helpers\" exclusion\n+(now R8 below).\n+\n+**Eligible (World-only, user-visible, fits the current `Action` contract,\n+submits from normal production state).**\n+\n+- **E1. `SetTimeScale` driven by a `Ctrl+\u003cdigit\u003e` keyboard preset that maps\n+  to a non-default speed.** Evidence:\n+  - `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs:149вЂ“241` defines\n+    `SetTimeScale` as a production `Action` whose `apply`/`revert` call\n+    `world.insert_resource(TimeScale::with_value(...))` вЂ” pure World-resource\n+    mutation, byte-identical revert.\n+  - `EditorShell::set_time_scale(value)` (commands.rs:348вЂ“382) already\n+    submits it through `CommandBus::submit` via\n+    `self.submit_action(Box::new(SetTimeScale::new(from, to)))` against\n+    `self.world.kernel_mut()`.\n+  - The user-visible trigger does not yet exist вЂ” `lifecycle/mod.rs:1676вЂ“1723`\u0027s\n+    `KeyboardInput` branch today routes only `Ctrl+Z`/`Y`/`S` (Undo/Redo/\n+    MarkSaved), `Space`/`Escape` (playback, bus-free), and plain `R`\n+    (asset reload, bus-free); no key binding currently calls\n+    `self.set_time_scale(...)`.\n+  - **Critical correction vs. the prior EXEC:** the binding\u0027s target value\n+    must be **non-default** (i.e. != `TimeScale::DEFAULT` = 1.0) so the\n+    no-op short-circuit at commands.rs:366 does NOT fire on the very first\n+    press from a fresh editor. CL-9 and CL-10 establish that production\n+    code never makes `TimeScale` non-default today, so a `Ctrl+0` в†’\n+    `TimeScale::DEFAULT` reset would always be a no-op on first press and\n+    never submit. The eligible binding shape must therefore set `TimeScale`\n+    to some non-default value (e.g. 2.0 вЂ” \"double speed\") on first press.\n+  - World-only вњ“; user-visible вњ“; fits current `Action` contract verbatim вњ“;\n+    no editor-state, no egui, no CAD, no asset reload, no watcher touched.\n+  - Non-noop on first press from fresh editor: вњ“ (1.0 в†’ 2.0 differs by\n+    1.0 \u003e\u003e f32::EPSILON).\n+\n+**Rejected (touch an excluded mutation surface, are non-user-visible, or\n+cannot satisfy the non-noop-from-fresh-state criterion).**\n+\n+- **R0 (new, replacing the prior Q2 `Ctrl+0` reset-to-default).**\n+  `Ctrl+\u003cdigit\u003e` в†’ `EditorShell::set_time_scale(TimeScale::DEFAULT)` (i.e.\n+  reset-to-default). Rejection reason: the proposed call is structurally\n+  fine (would mutate only `World`\u0027s `TimeScale` resource), but **CL-9 and\n+  CL-10 prove no production caller can make `TimeScale` non-default before\n+  the user presses the binding**, so on first press from a fresh editor\n+  `from == to == 1.0`, the `(to - from).abs() \u003c f32::EPSILON` short-circuit\n+  at `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs:366` fires, and\n+  `submit_action` is never called. Therefore a reset-to-default binding\n+  is not a user-visible *submitting* CommandBus action from normal\n+  production state and is rejected for Q2. (The action *type* `SetTimeScale`\n+  remains eligible вЂ” see E1; only the *reset-to-default* binding shape is\n+  rejected.)\n+- **R1. Mouse left-click face pick** вЂ” `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:1641вЂ“1666`\n+  в†’ `crates/editor-shell/src/pick_path.rs:58вЂ“121`. Mutates\n+  `self.coord.face_selection: editor_state::FaceSelectionSet` and\n+  `self.highlight_index_buffer: Option\u003crge_gfx::IndexBuffer\u003e` (excluded\n+  surfaces: `editor-state`, `FaceSelection`, render-path state).\n+- **R2. Toolbar `handle_button(ToolbarButtonId)`** вЂ” Play/Pause/Stop/Step/\n+  FrameStep. `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:1126вЂ“1180` and\n+  `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/playback.rs:5` (\"No CommandBus\n+  involvement; no new ECS state; no toolbar UI.\"). Mutates\n+  `EditorShell::{state, snapshot, audit}` вЂ” editor coordination, not\n+  `World` resources. Bus-free is the documented design.\n+- **R3. `EditorPlaybackCommand` (`Space`/`Escape`)** вЂ” same surface as R2;\n+  explicitly bus-free per `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/playback.rs:5`.\n+- **R4. Plain `R` вЂ” asset hot-reload** вЂ” `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:1710вЂ“1721`,\n+  `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/asset_reload.rs:29вЂ“119`. Mutates\n+  render-path state, watcher state, `cad-core` `CadGraph` вЂ” all excluded.\n+- **R5. GLB watcher tick** вЂ” `editor/rge-editor/src/main.rs:704вЂ“724`. Not\n+  user action (background drain); mutates watcher + render-path state.\n+- **R6. `WindowEvent::CursorMoved` + `WindowEvent::ModifiersChanged`** вЂ”\n+  `lifecycle/mod.rs:1634вЂ“1640, 1668вЂ“1675`. Bookkeeping only; not a user\n+  command; no undo semantics.\n+- **R7. egui inspector / dock \"slider\" path** вЂ” `crates/editor-shell/src/inspector.rs`\n+  + `crates/editor-state/src/inspector_snapshot.rs:1вЂ“117` (read-only\n+  aggregator) + `lifecycle/mod.rs:533вЂ“554`, `render_path.rs:289вЂ“298`\n+  (publish `Arc\u003cInspectorHandoff\u003e` to host). No production back-channel\n+  from `EguiHost` to `EditorShell::set_time_scale` / `submit_action`; the\n+  inspector module doc defers the consumer side to `editor-ui`. Wiring a\n+  back-channel would also drag in egui-state / `DockState` / handoff\n+  coupling вЂ” TASK exclusion list (\"egui state\", \"`DockState`\") rejects it.\n+- **R8. Test-only paths and `#[cfg(test)]` stubs** вЂ” all `tests/*.rs`\n+  under `crates/editor-shell/` and `crates/editor-actions/` plus the\n+  `#[cfg(test)]` `SetTag` / `FailAction` / `InsertVal` / `ReplaceVal` /\n+  `InsertMarker` impls in the production source files. Excluded as\n+  \"tests, stubs, inactive helpers\".\n+- **R9 (new, paired with the corrected R0 classification).**\n+  `CompoundAction`-driven user-visible binding. `CompoundAction`\n+  (`crates/editor-actions/src/compound.rs:51`) is production infrastructure\n+  per P2 above, but it has no user-visible production constructor today\n+  (CL-8: zero matches outside test code). Wiring \"the first user-visible\n+  `CompoundAction`\" would require *also* picking the first inner action\n+  *and* a user-visible trigger, expanding the scope beyond the smallest-\n+  pick criterion. Rejected as not a single-step smallest pick.\n+\n+### Q2. Smallest Pick\n+\n+**Bind `Ctrl+2` to set the `TimeScale` resource to `2.0` (a fixed non-default\n+\"double speed\" preset) via the existing `SetTimeScale` action and\n+`CommandBus::submit`.**\n+\n+This replaces the prior EXEC\u0027s invalid `Ctrl+0` reset-to-default pick per\n+CORRECT finding #1.\n+\n+Why this is non-noop from normal production state (the criterion the prior\n+pick failed):\n+- CL-10 establishes `TimeScale == TimeScale::DEFAULT == 1.0` for every fresh\n+  editor in production today (no caller makes it otherwise).\n+- Pressing `Ctrl+2` calls `self.set_time_scale(2.0)` (commands.rs:348).\n+- `from = self.time_scale().value() = 1.0`; `to = TimeScale::with_value(2.0).value() = 2.0`.\n+- `(to - from).abs() = 1.0`, which is NOT `\u003c f32::EPSILON`. The short-circuit\n+  at commands.rs:366 does NOT fire.\n+- Therefore `self.submit_action(Box::new(SetTimeScale::new(1.0, 2.0)))` runs.\n+- The bus routes through `self.command_bus.submit(action, self.world.kernel_mut())`\n+  (commands.rs:257) вЂ” a real, non-noop `CommandBus::submit` from normal\n+  production state. вњ“\n+\n+Why this is the smallest among the corrected-eligible candidates:\n+- The production `Action` impl already exists (`SetTimeScale`, fully implemented).\n+- The shell wrapper already exists (`EditorShell::set_time_scale(value)`).\n+- The keyboard branch (`lifecycle/mod.rs:1676вЂ“1723`) already exists, gates on\n+  `!egui_consumed`, and already dispatches modifier-bound `EditorKeyCommand`s.\n+- `KeyCode::Digit2` exists (CL-11) and is unbound today (CL-12).\n+- The only missing pieces are: one new enum variant + one match arm in\n+  `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press` + one match arm in\n+  `EditorShell::handle_key_command` that calls `self.set_time_scale(2.0)`.\n+- No new types, no new crate, no new file, no Cargo edit, no trait widening,\n+  no `editor-actions` change at all.\n+- Mutation surface is exactly one `World` resource (`TimeScale`).\n+\n+Alternative-but-larger eligible bindings (documented for completeness; NOT the\n+Q2 selection):\n+- `Ctrl+]` / `Ctrl+[` вЂ” step time-scale up/down by a fixed factor. Two\n+  bindings, two map arms, two dispatch arms, plus a step constant and a\n+  `self.time_scale().value() В± step` read. Strictly larger.\n+- `Ctrl+1` + `Ctrl+2` + `Ctrl+3` preset trio. Three bindings, three map\n+  arms, three dispatch arms. Strictly larger.\n+- `Ctrl+0` reset-to-default ONLY after first wiring a non-default preset\n+  (e.g. `Ctrl+2`). Requires composing two changes; bigger than the single\n+  preset alone, and the reset half is only meaningful once a non-default\n+  preset exists in production. The smallest single first action is therefore\n+  the single non-default preset binding; reset-to-default is a sensible\n+  follow-up after the first preset ships.\n+\n+### Q3. Implementation Shape\n+\n+Approach A only вЂ” World-only `Action` surface, no `editor-actions` dependency\n+promotion, no editor-wide command context, no adapter-layer dual ledger, no\n+Cargo changes, no mutation outside `rge_kernel_ecs::World` plus the already-\n+established dual-ledger audit + dirty-flag behaviour that\n+`EditorShell::set_time_scale` already encodes today.\n+\n+Concrete shape (covers the corrected `Ctrl+2 в†’ set_time_scale(2.0)` pick from\n+Q2; no Q3 description of the rejected `Ctrl+0` reset variant is retained per\n+CORRECT finding #1):\n+\n+1. **Extend `EditorKeyCommand`** in `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs`\n+   with one new variant вЂ” name it `SetTimeScaleDoubleSpeed` (single tuple-unit\n+   variant; carries no payload because the target value is the constant\n+   `2.0_f32`). This is additive on a closed enum whose own doc-comment\n+   explicitly endorses extension (\"Future editor keybinds (Play/Stop, selection\n+   clear, tool switch) extend this enum rather than growing parallel command\n+   channels\").\n+2. **Extend `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press`** in the same file (lines\n+   ~101вЂ“113) with one arm that maps `(KeyCode::Digit2, ctrl=true,\n+   shift=false)` to `Some(Self::SetTimeScaleDoubleSpeed)`. The existing\n+   `!ctrl || shift` early-return already filters bad modifier combinations;\n+   the new arm is one literal pattern match. CL-11/CL-12 confirm\n+   `KeyCode::Digit2` exists in `rge_input` and is unbound today.\n+3. **Extend `EditorShell::handle_key_command`** in the same file (lines\n+   307вЂ“327) with one match arm that calls `self.set_time_scale(2.0)`. The\n+   existing `set_time_scale` method already (a) captures `from`, (b) clamps\n+   `to` via `TimeScale::with_value`, (c) skips no-ops via `f32::EPSILON`,\n+   (d) builds `Box\u003cSetTimeScale\u003e`, (e) submits through\n+   `self.command_bus.submit(action, self.world.kernel_mut())`, (f) records\n+   a `TimeScaleChanged` audit event on the shell\u0027s own ring buffer. All six\n+   lines of supporting logic already exist; the new arm is a single call.\n+4. **No other source edits.** `crates/editor-actions/**` is not touched вЂ”\n+   `Action`, `CommandBus`, `BusEntry`, `BusError`, `ActionResult`, `ActionId`,\n+   `MergeOutcome`, **and `CompoundAction`** all remain on their current\n+   `\u0026mut rge_kernel_ecs::World` surface with no changes.\n+   `crates/editor-state/**` is not touched. `editor/rge-editor/**` is not\n+   touched (the binary already forwards `WindowEvent` to the shell unchanged;\n+   the new binding falls out for free via CL-13). `kernel/ecs/**` is not\n+   touched.\n+5. **No Cargo, no manifest, no lockfile, no feature flag, no workspace, no\n+   lint-config, no doctrine edit.** All needed dependencies (`rge_editor_actions`,\n+   `rge_input`, `rge_kernel_ecs`) are already in `crates/editor-shell/Cargo.toml`.\n+6. **Mutation envelope is World-only.** The bus call advances\n+   `rge_kernel_ecs::World`\u0027s `TimeScale` resource via\n+   `World::insert_resource(TimeScale::with_value(2.0))`. The bus\u0027s internal\n+   audit ledger records one `EventKind::Action` event (with `SetTimeScale::payload()`\n+   bytes = `2.0_f32.to_le_bytes()`). The undo-stack cursor advances by one.\n+   `is_dirty()` flips to `true` (was `false` immediately after `mark_saved`).\n+   The shell\u0027s own `audit.record(AuditEvent::TimeScaleChanged { from: 1.0,\n+   to: 2.0 })` runs once. Every effect is either a `World` mutation or an\n+   already-established side effect of the existing `set_time_scale` method вЂ”\n+   no new authority.\n+7. **Coalesce semantics already correct.** `SetTimeScale::id()` returns the\n+   constant `\"set-time-scale\"`; pressing `Ctrl+2` twice within 500 ms\n+   coalesces into one stack entry (and the second press is independently a\n+   no-op via the short-circuit because `from == to == 2.0` after the first\n+   press lands). Either way: one stack entry whose revert restores 1.0. No\n+   additional design required.\n+8. **No-op semantics already correct on repeat press.** Once `TimeScale` is\n+   at `2.0`, pressing `Ctrl+2` again hits `(to - from).abs() == 0.0 \u003c f32::EPSILON`\n+   and short-circuits with no submit / no audit / no dirty flip. This is\n+   correct UX and was already the established semantics for the existing\n+   `set_time_scale` method.\n+\n+### Q4. Verification Plan\n+\n+Read-only evidence to gather **before** the future implementation task fires:\n+\n+- Confirm `rge_input::KeyCode::Digit2` is still the variant name for the `2`\n+  key (verified in this preflight at CL-11: `crates/input/src/keyboard.rs:84`).\n+  The implementation task should re-verify with a one-line `rg -n\n+  \"Digit2\" crates/input/src/keyboard.rs` immediately before implementing.\n+- Confirm there is no existing `Ctrl+2` binding that the new variant would\n+  shadow (verified in this preflight at CL-12: zero matches for\n+  `KeyCode::Digit` in `crates/editor-shell/src` or `editor/rge-editor/src`).\n+- Confirm `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press` (`crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs:101вЂ“113`)\n+  and `EditorShell::handle_key_command` (commands.rs:307вЂ“327) have not been\n+  moved or renamed in the interim.\n+\n+Verification gates the future implementation dispatch MUST run (this preflight\n+runs **none** of them):\n+\n+- `cargo build -p rge-editor-shell` вЂ” confirms the new variant + match arms\n+  compile.\n+- `cargo +nightly fmt --check -p rge-editor-shell` (or workspace fmt-check\n+  per local convention).\n+- `cargo clippy -p rge-editor-shell --all-targets -- -D warnings`.\n+- `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test keyboard_command_bus_round_trip` вЂ”\n+  the existing `Ctrl+Z`/`Y`/`S` round-trip test pattern is the natural\n+  extension point for a `Ctrl+2` в†’ `set_time_scale(2.0)` round-trip case.\n+- `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test time_scale_test` вЂ” the existing\n+  `set_time_scale_routes_through_bus_and_undo_redo_round_trips` test\n+  already exercises the bus path; the new keyboard-driven case should\n+  reuse the same headless harness via\n+  `EditorShell::handle_key_command(EditorKeyCommand::SetTimeScaleDoubleSpeed)`\n+  (the doc-comment already states \"Public so headless tests can drive the\n+  bus without synthesizing winit `KeyEvent`s\").\n+- `cargo test --workspace --no-fail-fast` вЂ” workspace regression sweep.\n+- `cargo run -q -p rge-tool-architecture-lints -- all` вЂ” confirms no\n+  architecture-lint posture changes (no new `forbidden-dep` violations, no\n+  `editor-state-ownership` violations, no `editor-actions` tier shift).\n+- `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` вЂ” the canonical dispatch verification gate.\n+\n+Likely focused tests the future implementation should add (read-only opinion;\n+the implementor decides):\n+\n+- One test pinning `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press(KeyCode::Digit2,\n+  ctrl=true, shift=false) == Some(EditorKeyCommand::SetTimeScaleDoubleSpeed)`,\n+  and that `shift=true` / `ctrl=false` return `None` (existing modifier-gate\n+  invariant preserved).\n+- One test that builds an `EditorShell` (default `TimeScale` = 1.0), calls\n+  `shell.handle_key_command(EditorKeyCommand::SetTimeScaleDoubleSpeed)`, and\n+  asserts the `TimeScale` resource reads `2.0` plus the bus\u0027s `stack().cursor()`\n+  advanced by 1 plus `command_bus().is_dirty() == true` plus the shell-side\n+  audit ledger gained one `TimeScaleChanged { from: 1.0, to: 2.0 }` event.\n+- One test that asserts `shell.undo_command()` immediately after a\n+  `SetTimeScaleDoubleSpeed` press restores `TimeScale` to `1.0` byte-identically\n+  and `is_dirty()` returns to `false` only after a subsequent\n+  `mark_saved_command()` aligns the cursor with the saved point.\n+- One test that asserts pressing `Ctrl+2` a SECOND time (with `TimeScale`\n+  already at `2.0`) is a no-op (no cursor advance, no dirty flip, no audit-\n+  event append) вЂ” this exercises the existing no-op short-circuit on a new\n+  caller, and is the same property the rejected `Ctrl+0` reset would have\n+  exhibited on EVERY press from fresh state.\n+\n+### Q5. Follow-Up Task Surface\n+\n+Exactly one smallest follow-up implementation task. Bound it like this when\n+the Planner writes the TASK packet:\n+\n+- **Goal.** Wire `Ctrl+2` to set `TimeScale` to `2.0` (the \"double speed\"\n+  preset) through `CommandBus::submit(SetTimeScale, World)`. Achieve \"first\n+  user-visible CommandBus action that calls `submit` from normal production\n+  state\" by extending the existing `EditorKeyCommand` enum and the existing\n+  `EditorShell::handle_key_command` dispatch. This replaces the prior EXEC\u0027s\n+  invalid `Ctrl+0` reset-to-default pick per CORRECT finding #1.\n+- **MAY edit (allowed file surface).**\n+  - `crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/commands.rs` вЂ” add one\n+    `EditorKeyCommand::SetTimeScaleDoubleSpeed` variant; add one arm to\n+    `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press` matching `(KeyCode::Digit2, ctrl=true,\n+    shift=false)`; add one arm to `EditorShell::handle_key_command` that\n+    calls `self.set_time_scale(2.0)`.\n+  - `crates/editor-shell/tests/keyboard_command_bus_round_trip.rs` and/or\n+    `crates/editor-shell/tests/time_scale_test.rs` вЂ” extend with the\n+    focused-test cases from Q4. New file allowed only if extending the\n+    existing ones is structurally awkward; prefer extension.\n+- **MUST NOT touch.**\n+  - `crates/editor-actions/**` вЂ” no trait widening, no bus signature change,\n+    no payload format change, no `BusEntry` variant addition, no `ActionId`\n+    rename, no `CompoundAction` change. (Per CORRECT finding #2, the corrected\n+    inventory acknowledges `CompoundAction` as production infrastructure;\n+    the implementation task does NOT use it because composing user-visible\n+    actions atomically is out of scope for the first single-action wire.)\n+  - `crates/editor-state/**` вЂ” no coordination-category change, no\n+    editor-state-ownership lint change.\n+  - `editor/rge-editor/**` вЂ” the binary forwards `WindowEvent` to the shell\n+    unchanged; do not touch `main.rs`.\n+  - `kernel/ecs/**` вЂ” no `World` API change, no new `Resource` type, no\n+    kernel-level edits.\n+  - Any `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, workspace manifest, feature flag, or\n+    dependency declaration.\n+  - Any architecture-lint configuration, doctrine document, ADR, `plans/`\n+    markdown, `.gitignore`, or repository-metadata file.\n+  - Any existing handoff packet (including this EXEC, the prior EXEC, the\n+    TASK, and the CORRECT).\n+  - Any GitHub issue, label, PR, branch, commit, or remote state.\n+  - `crates/editor-shell/src/{pick_path.rs, audit.rs, snapshot.rs,\n+    render_path.rs, render_input.rs, render_frame_e2e_perf.rs, viewport.rs,\n+    coord.rs, camera.rs, play_state.rs, play_toolbar.rs, time_scale.rs,\n+    world.rs, inspector.rs, visual_smoke.rs, visual_test_harness.rs,\n+    lifecycle/playback.rs, lifecycle/asset_reload.rs, lifecycle/mod.rs}` вЂ”\n+    none of these need to change for `Ctrl+2` в†’ set-to-2.0.\n+    (`lifecycle/mod.rs`\u0027s `KeyboardInput` branch already dispatches\n+    `EditorKeyCommand` and falls through correctly; the new variant flows\n+    for free.)\n+- **Verification gates.** Run, in order: `cargo build -p rge-editor-shell`;\n+  `cargo +nightly fmt --check -p rge-editor-shell` (or local workspace\n+  equivalent); `cargo clippy -p rge-editor-shell --all-targets -- -D warnings`;\n+  `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test keyboard_command_bus_round_trip`;\n+  `cargo test -p rge-editor-shell --test time_scale_test`;\n+  `cargo test --workspace --no-fail-fast`;\n+  `cargo run -q -p rge-tool-architecture-lints -- all`;\n+  `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1`. All gates must pass before close-out.\n+- **Halt conditions.** Halt and request fresh guidance if any of the\n+  following occur:\n+  - `rge_input::KeyCode::Digit2` has been renamed/removed since this\n+    preflight, OR an existing `Ctrl+2` binding is discovered that would be\n+    shadowed.\n+  - `EditorKeyCommand`, `EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press`, or\n+    `EditorShell::handle_key_command` have been moved, renamed, or\n+    restructured since this preflight (re-read before implementing).\n+  - Implementing the binding requires editing\n+    `crates/editor-actions/src/{action.rs, bus.rs, lib.rs, compound.rs}` or\n+    touching the `Action`-trait signature, the `CommandBus::submit`\n+    signature, or any non-`World` mutation surface.\n+  - Any verification gate fails for a reason other than the new test case\n+    being incomplete (e.g. architecture lint flips, `forbidden-dep`\n+    violation, workspace test regression).\n+  - A new Cargo dependency, feature flag, or workspace edit becomes necessary.\n+  - The implementation cannot be completed without widening\n+    `EditorKeyCommand` beyond one new variant + one new map arm + one new\n+    dispatch arm, indicating a scope miscarve.\n+  - The audit-only conclusions of this preflight are contradicted by\n+    current code state вЂ” specifically, if a production caller of\n+    `EditorShell::set_time_scale` has appeared in the interim (the \"first\n+    submitting action from normal production state\" premise would be\n+    re-stale in the other direction, and the smallest pick might need to\n+    shift again).\n+  - The dual-ledger semantics (bus\u0027s internal `AuditLedger` + shell\u0027s\n+    `audit` ring buffer) have been consolidated since this preflight; the\n+    test asserting the shell-side `TimeScaleChanged` event would need to be\n+    re-scoped.\n+\n+## Deviations from Task Packet\n+\n+None вЂ” execution stayed strictly within the Task Packet scope as narrowed by\n+the CORRECT packet. No source, tests, docs, manifests, Cargo files, scripts,\n+schemas, status files, workflows, lint configs, doctrine documents, prior\n+packets (TASK, prior EXEC, CORRECT), or GitHub state were edited or added;\n+only this single corrected EXEC report was created. No cargo / test /\n+formatter / architecture-lint / benchmark / doctest / `cargo-deny` /\n+`.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` / source-generation / docs-generation command was\n+run.\n+\n+The three CORRECT-packet findings are addressed in full:\n+\n+1. **CORRECT #1 вЂ” invalid `Ctrl+0` reset premise.** Addressed by (a) Q1\u0027s\n+   new R0 rejection (\"reset-to-default is no-op from fresh state, evidenced\n+   by CL-9 and CL-10\"), (b) Q2\u0027s replacement pick `Ctrl+2 в†’ set_time_scale(2.0)`,\n+   (c) Q3 describing only the corrected `Ctrl+2 в†’ 2.0` implementation shape,\n+   (d) Q5 naming `Ctrl+2 в†’ set_time_scale(2.0)` as the bounded follow-up.\n+   The non-noop, user-visible, World-only submit path IS evidenced (see\n+   \"HC вЂ” non-noop ... submit path evidenced\" above), so the report does NOT\n+   route to `NEEDS_HUMAN`.\n+2. **CORRECT #2 вЂ” production `Action` inventory.** Addressed by Q1\u0027s\n+   \"Production `Action` implementations in the audited roots\" subsection\n+   listing both `SetTimeScale` (commands.rs:170) and `CompoundAction`\n+   (compound.rs:51). `CompoundAction` is classified as production\n+   infrastructure / non-candidate because it has no user-visible production\n+   constructor in the audited roots (CL-8). The prior EXEC\u0027s claim that\n+   `SetTimeScale` is \"the only production `Action` impl\" is corrected.\n+3. **CORRECT #3 вЂ” search/tooling log accuracy.** Addressed by the new\n+   \"Tooling vocabulary\" subsection and the per-entry `(shell: ...)` /\n+   `(agent: ...)` tagging in the Command Log. The prior EXEC\u0027s\n+   command-log entries are re-classified inline (prior CL В§1, В§3 = shell;\n+   prior CL В§4 = agent: Glob; prior CL В§6\u0027s `command -v rg` + `rg --files`\n+   claim corrected to agent-tool inventory only; prior CL В§В§21вЂ“30 = agent:\n+   Grep; prior CL В§В§7вЂ“20, 23 = agent: Read). This round actually runs shell\n+   `command -v rg`, shell `rg --files`, shell `rg -n` (CL-2 through CL-4,\n+   CL-7 through CL-12) so the corrected claims are grounded in real shell\n+   invocations on this host.\n+\n+## Open Questions for Reviewer\n+\n+- Q2\u0027s \"`2.0`\" preset is chosen as the smallest concrete non-default value\n+  to bind. If the project\u0027s UX convention prefers a different first preset\n+  (e.g. `Ctrl+1` в†’ 1.0 plus `Ctrl+2` в†’ 2.0 as a matched pair, or `Ctrl+]`\n+  step-up instead of a fixed preset), the human arbiter can substitute one\n+  for the other in the follow-up TASK packet without changing the Approach-A\n+  implementation shape. The trade-off (single fixed preset vs preset\n+  trio vs step binding) is documented in Q2\u0027s \"Alternative-but-larger\"\n+  list. The decisive criterion вЂ” submits from normal production state with\n+  `from = TimeScale::DEFAULT = 1.0`, `to != 1.0` вЂ” is satisfied by any\n+  binding whose target value differs from `TimeScale::DEFAULT`; the\n+  reviewer may swap `2.0` for any non-1.0 value in `[TimeScale::MIN,\n+  TimeScale::MAX]` without invalidating the audit conclusions.\n+- `CompoundAction` is classified as production infrastructure /\n+  non-candidate (Q1 P2 + R9). If the reviewer prefers to instead route the\n+  first user-visible CommandBus action through a `CompoundAction` wrapping\n+  a single inner `SetTimeScale` (to \"pre-seed\" the composite path), the\n+  smallest binding shape would still be `Ctrl+2`, but it would wrap the\n+  `SetTimeScale` in `CompoundAction::new(\"set-time-scale-compound\",\n+  ActionId::new(\"set-time-scale-compound\"))` + `push(Box::new(...))` вЂ”\n+  strictly more code than the direct `SetTimeScale` submit, so this\n+  preflight does NOT recommend it. The non-compound direct submit is the\n+  smallest non-noop user-visible World-only path.\n+- The audit deliberately did not re-inspect `crates/cad-core/**`,\n+  `crates/cad-projection/**`, `crates/editor-egui-host/**`, or any\n+  `editor-ui` crate. They are outside ISSUE-132\u0027s five-root scope and are\n+  not needed to answer the corrected Q1вЂ“Q5 under the World-only / Approach-A\n+  constraint.\n+\n+## Worktree State\n+\n+- Tracked files: clean.\n+- Untracked items: the pre-existing `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_TASK_2026-05-23_22-32-44+0300.md`\n+  + `.meta.json` sidecar; `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_22-42-34+0300.md`\n+  + `.meta.json` sidecar (prior EXEC, preserved verbatim);\n+  `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_CORRECT_2026-05-23_22-55-20+0300.md` + `.meta.json`\n+  sidecar; and `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_2026-05-23_23-01-08+0300.md`\n+  (this corrected report; the only Executor-created change in this\n+  correction round). The EXEC sidecar will be created by\n+  `new-handoff.ps1 -Finalize`.\n+- Branch: `ai-dispatch/ISSUE-132`.\n+- Last commit: `cb63077` chore(dispatch): seed task #24 World-only CommandBus\n+  action preflight.\n+\n+---\n+\n+HANDOFF_STATUS: COMPLETE\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-132\n+AUTHOR: Executor / Claude\n+NEXT_ROLE: REVIEWER_AI\n+EXIT_CODE: 0\n+\n+---"
