        "patch":  "@@ -0,0 +1,153 @@\n+# Task Packet\n+\n+DISPATCH_ID: ISSUE-132\n+AUTHOR: Planner / OpenAI Codex\n+TIMESTAMP: 2026-05-23_22-32-44+0300\n+RELATED_FILES:\n+- crates/editor-actions/**\n+- crates/editor-shell/**\n+- editor/rge-editor/**\n+- crates/editor-state/**\n+- kernel/ecs/**\n+- ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_*.md\n+- ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_*.md\n+STATUS: OPEN\n+\n+## Goal\n+\n+Perform GitHub issue #132 as a read-only World-only CommandBus action preflight for task #24. The Executor must inspect the required editor-action, editor-shell, editor binary, editor-state, ECS, and prior ISSUE-108 execution-report surfaces; adopt ISSUE-108 Approach A, keeping the existing World-only `Action` direction fixed; and produce one evidence-backed EXEC report with a five-question answer block that names the smallest safe implementation task for the first World-only user-visible CommandBus editor action, or halts with `NEEDS_HUMAN` if no eligible candidate exists.\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+### MAY edit\n+- None. This is an audit-only dispatch.\n+\n+### MUST NOT edit\n+- `crates/editor-actions/**`\n+- `crates/editor-shell/**`\n+- `editor/rge-editor/**`\n+- `crates/editor-state/**`\n+- `kernel/ecs/**`\n+- Any source file.\n+- Any test file.\n+- Any `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, feature flag, dependency declaration, workspace manifest, or Cargo metadata file.\n+- Any script, schema, workflow, status file, doctrine document, ADR, lint configuration, `.gitignore`, generated artifact, persisted log, or repository metadata file.\n+- Any GitHub issue, label, PR, branch, commit, or remote state.\n+- Any existing handoff packet, including this TASK packet and `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_*.md`.\n+- Any handoff packet other than the single required `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_*.md` execution report.\n+\n+### MAY add new files\n+- Exactly one execution report matching `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_*.md`.\n+\n+### MUST NOT add new files\n+- New source files, tests, docs, fixtures, generated artifacts, persisted logs, screenshots, Cargo entries, dependency files, crates, architecture lints, schemas, scripts, workflow files, TASK packets, REVIEW packets, CORRECT packets, CLOSEOUT packets, issue notes, or design documents.\n+\n+## Deliverables\n+\n+- One `EXECUTION_REPORT` packet under `ai_handoffs/` and no other repository changes.\n+- A command log in the EXEC report listing every read/search/status command used for the preflight, including any fallback used because `rg` is unavailable.\n+- Mandatory read-only inspection of all required roots: `crates/editor-actions/**`, `crates/editor-shell/**`, `editor/rge-editor/**`, `crates/editor-state/**`, and `kernel/ecs/**`.\n+- Mandatory read-only inspection of `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_*.md`, with a short statement that Approach A from ISSUE-108 is adopted as the fixed architectural direction for this preflight.\n+- A candidate inventory that only considers user-visible actions whose mutation target can remain `rge_kernel_ecs::World`-only under the existing `Action::apply(\u0026mut World)` / `Action::revert(\u0026mut World)` and `CommandBus::submit(..., \u0026mut World)` contract.\n+- An explicit exclusion list for candidates rejected because they would mutate editor-state, selection, hover, active tool, `FaceSelection`, `DockState`, egui state, render-path state, asset-reload state, watcher state, or `cad-core` `CadGraph`.\n+- The exact answer section shown below, with all five headings present in this order:\n+\n+```markdown\n+## 5-Question World-only CommandBus Action Preflight Answer Block\n+\n+### Q1. Candidate Actions\n+\n+### Q2. Smallest Pick\n+\n+### Q3. Implementation Shape\n+\n+### Q4. Verification Plan\n+\n+### Q5. Follow-Up Task Surface\n+```\n+\n+- Q1 must identify every plausible World-only user-visible CommandBus action candidate found in the required roots, cite the code evidence for each, and classify each as eligible or rejected. Rejections must include the concrete excluded mutation surface or reason.\n+- Q2 must pick exactly one smallest eligible candidate, or say `NEEDS_HUMAN` if no eligible World-only user-visible candidate exists. Q2 must not propose widened editor-context actions or adapter-layer dual-ledger work as alternatives.\n+- Q3 must describe the implementation shape for the Q2 pick using ISSUE-108 Approach A only: existing World-only `Action` surface, no `editor-actions` dependency promotion, no editor-wide command context, no adapter-layer dual ledger, no Cargo changes, and no mutation outside `rge_kernel_ecs::World` plus any already-established audit/dirty behavior directly tied to that World-only action.\n+- Q4 must give a verification plan for the future implementation task. The plan may name future cargo/test/lint gates, but the Executor must not run them during this preflight. The plan must include read-only evidence needed before implementation and likely focused tests after implementation.\n+- Q5 must name exactly one smallest follow-up implementation task if Q2 found an eligible candidate. It must include allowed file surfaces, must-not-touch surfaces, verification gates, and halt conditions for that future implementation. If no candidate exists, Q5 must say `NEEDS_HUMAN` and name the smallest human decision needed.\n+\n+## Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+- The dispatch is audit-only. No source, tests, docs, manifests, lockfiles, workflows, scripts, schemas, doctrine files, status files, labels, issues, existing packets, or non-EXEC handoff packets are edited or added.\n+- Exactly one new EXEC packet is produced for this dispatch.\n+- The EXEC packet explicitly states this was a read-only World-only CommandBus action preflight and that no local cargo commands, tests, formatters, architecture lints, or `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1` were run.\n+- The EXEC packet documents read-only inspection of every mandatory root: `crates/editor-actions/**`, `crates/editor-shell/**`, `editor/rge-editor/**`, `crates/editor-state/**`, and `kernel/ecs/**`.\n+- The EXEC packet documents read-only inspection of `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_*.md` and states that ISSUE-108 Approach A, the World-only Action direction, is adopted for this task.\n+- The EXEC packet contains the exact `## 5-Question World-only CommandBus Action Preflight Answer Block` heading and the exact Q1-Q5 subheadings listed in `Deliverables`.\n+- Q1 includes only World-only user-visible candidates as eligible. Any candidate touching editor-state, selection, hover, active tool, `FaceSelection`, `DockState`, egui state, render-path state, asset-reload state, watcher state, or `cad-core` `CadGraph` is rejected.\n+- Q2 names exactly one smallest eligible World-only candidate, or says `NEEDS_HUMAN` if none exists.\n+- Q2 and Q3 do not propose ISSUE-108 Approach B, tier-2 promotion of `editor-actions`, or ISSUE-108 Approach C, adapter-layer dual ledger, as alternatives.\n+- Q3 describes an Approach A implementation shape only and does not require Cargo changes, trait widening, new crates, architecture-doctrine edits, or non-World mutation authority.\n+- Q4 is a verification plan only; no local cargo, test, formatter, architecture-lint, or dispatch verification command is run by this preflight.\n+- Q5 names exactly one smallest implementation task with allowed files, must-not-touch surfaces, verification gates, and halt conditions, or reports `NEEDS_HUMAN`.\n+- If no World-only user-visible action candidate exists, the EXEC report must halt with header `STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, include an explicit line `EXEC_STATUS: blocked`, set footer `HANDOFF_STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, route `NEXT_ROLE: HUMAN_ARBITER`, and make Q5 say `NEEDS_HUMAN`.\n+- If an eligible candidate exists and the audit succeeds, the EXEC report footer contains exactly one line-anchored `HANDOFF_STATUS: COMPLETE` marker and routes `NEXT_ROLE: REVIEWER_AI`.\n+\n+## Constraints / Non-Goals\n+\n+- This dispatch is a read-only preflight. It must not implement a CommandBus action, wire UI/input, alter action traits, add command context, add adapters, migrate commands, alter render invalidation, or update tests.\n+- ISSUE-108 Approach A is fixed for this task. Do not reopen the ISSUE-108 comparison, do not propose Approach B as an alternative, and do not propose Approach C as an alternative in Q2 or Q3.\n+- Do not run local cargo commands, tests, formatters, architecture lints, benchmarks, doctests, cargo-deny, source generation, docs generation, or `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1`.\n+- Do not run `cargo check`, `cargo build`, `cargo test`, `cargo fmt`, `cargo clippy`, `cargo run -p rge-tool-architecture-lints`, or any equivalent command.\n+- Do not edit source, tests, docs, `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, workflows, scripts, schemas, doctrine, status files, lint files, existing packets, labels, issues, PRs, branches, commits, or any non-EXEC file.\n+- Do not create a follow-up TASK packet, REVIEW packet, CORRECT packet, CLOSEOUT packet, issue comment, PR comment, design doc, ADR, code comment, commit, branch, PR, or GitHub issue.\n+- Do not broaden the audit into CAD operator design, render-path implementation, asset reload, file watching, egui dock internals, architecture-lint policy, CI, or generalized command-context architecture.\n+- Do not treat tests, stubs, inactive helpers, render-only observers, asset reload, watchers, face selection, editor coordination state, or `cad-core` graph mutation as eligible candidates for this World-only task.\n+\n+## Verification Gates\n+\n+The Executor MUST run and document each applicable gate in the `EXECUTION_REPORT`. These gates are read/search/status only:\n+\n+- Run `git status --short --untracked-files=no` before the audit. Document any pre-existing tracked changes. If tracked changes inside the audit surfaces make read-only conclusions unreliable, halt with `NEEDS_HUMAN`; do not clean or revert them.\n+- Inventory files under the mandatory audit roots. Use `rg --files crates/editor-actions crates/editor-shell editor/rge-editor crates/editor-state kernel/ecs` if `rg` is available; otherwise use an equivalent PowerShell recursive file listing.\n+- Confirm each mandatory audit root exists and was inspected: `crates/editor-actions/**`, `crates/editor-shell/**`, `editor/rge-editor/**`, `crates/editor-state/**`, and `kernel/ecs/**`.\n+- Locate and read `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-108_EXEC_*.md`. If more than one match exists, read the newest by timestamp and document which one was used.\n+- Search the mandatory audit roots for current World-only CommandBus contract evidence. Suggested patterns include `CommandBus`, `CommandBus::submit`, `submit_action`, `trait Action`, `impl Action`, `Action::apply`, `Action::revert`, `World`, `insert_resource`, `insert`, `remove`, `UndoStack`, `AuditLedger`, `is_dirty`, and `mark_saved`.\n+- Search the mandatory audit roots for user-visible input or command surfaces that could drive a World-only action. Suggested patterns include `WindowEvent`, `KeyboardInput`, `MouseInput`, `ElementState`, `KeyCode`, `translate_keyboard`, `handle_key_command`, `handle_button`, `set_time_scale`, `TimeScale`, `toolbar`, `inspector`, `slider`, `button`, `click`, `shortcut`, and `submit_action`.\n+- Search the mandatory audit roots for excluded mutation surfaces and document why any matching candidate is rejected. Suggested patterns include `editor_state`, `selection`, `Selection`, `hover`, `Hover`, `active_tool`, `ActiveTool`, `FaceSelection`, `face_selection`, `DockState`, `egui`, `render_path`, `asset_reload`, `watcher`, `glb_watcher`, `CadGraph`, and `cad_graph`.\n+- Read the files necessary to answer Q1-Q5, including the current `crates/editor-actions` CommandBus and `Action` files, current editor-shell command/input files, current editor-state coordination files needed for exclusions, current editor binary event/watcher entry points needed for exclusions, and relevant ECS `World`/resource files.\n+- Record every grep/search and read command used in the EXEC report.\n+- Confirm the EXEC report contains the exact `## 5-Question World-only CommandBus Action Preflight Answer Block` heading and exact Q1-Q5 subheadings listed in `Deliverables`.\n+- Run `git status --short` after writing the EXEC packet. Expected result: no Executor-created changes outside the single new `ai_handoffs/ISSUE-132_EXEC_*.md` report, aside from any pre-existing changes documented before the audit.\n+\n+No local cargo build, cargo check, cargo test, cargo fmt, cargo clippy, cargo-deny, benchmark, architecture-lint run, `.ai/dispatch.verify.ps1`, source generation, docs generation, or manual verification beyond read/search/status commands is allowed for this audit-only dispatch.\n+\n+## Halt Conditions\n+\n+The Executor MUST halt without editing existing files and request fresh guidance if any of the following occur:\n+\n+- No World-only user-visible action candidate exists after inspecting the required roots and ISSUE-108 EXEC report. In this case the EXEC report must use header `STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, include `EXEC_STATUS: blocked`, footer `HANDOFF_STATUS: NEEDS_HUMAN`, `NEXT_ROLE: HUMAN_ARBITER`, and Q5 `NEEDS_HUMAN`.\n+- Every plausible user-visible candidate requires mutating editor-state, selection, hover, active tool, `FaceSelection`, `DockState`, egui state, render-path state, asset-reload state, watcher state, or `cad-core` `CadGraph`.\n+- The smallest candidate would require widening `Action` beyond `\u0026mut rge_kernel_ecs::World`, promoting `editor-actions` to a tier-2 editor-domain crate, adding adapter-layer dual ledger authority, adding a Cargo dependency, or changing architecture doctrine.\n+- A production user-visible World-only CommandBus action is already fully wired, making the \"first action\" implementation premise stale.\n+- Answering Q1-Q5 requires editing source, tests, docs, manifests, workflows, scripts, schemas, doctrine, status files, existing packets, labels, issues, or any file other than the single EXEC report.\n+- A required audit root or `ai_